doug@knowpeace.com wrote:
> 
<snip>
> 1) Is everybody adding the 100uf 16 volt capacitor to prevent
>    power dips (per http://www.robotics.com/arobot/sonar.html)?
I've heard that the 100uF cap isn't needed when using the HB's
standard battery source ... but since I was soldering on the
Polaroid board anyway, I decided that it wouldn't hurt to add
it.  Do be *sure* to add the 0.1 uF cap at C7 as per:
http://el.www.media.mit.edu/projects/handy-board/software/sonar.html
<snip>
> 
> 2) I like the "cap" around the transducer as illustrated in
>    this picture of the "RadStamp"
Since most of my constructions are LEGO based, I attached my
transducer to a LEGO 40-tooth gear using a couple of dabs of
rubber cement.
<snip>
> 
